Daikibo Machine Performance Summary

Total Downtime: 1,030 minutes | Total Breakdowns: 103 incidents

Worst Machine: LaserWelder (both by downtime and breakdown frequency)

Key Findings:

Critical, Localized Failure (“Biggest Fire”)

Location: Seiko factory, Osaka

Cause: Single LaserWelder machine

Impact: 480 minutes of downtime

Action: Immediate maintenance or replacement

Systemic, Widespread Issue (“Next Fire”)

Frequent failures: LaserWelder (48) and LaserCutter (43)

Emerging risk across multiple factories

Action: Proactive maintenance program for all units

Strategic Recommendation:

Reactive: Fix the LaserWelder at Seiko immediately.

Proactive: Audit and maintain all LaserWelder and LaserCutter machines to prevent future downtime.

Conclusion: Addressing the critical machine now and preventing systemic failures ensures both immediate productivity recovery and long-term reliability.
